      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Modern historians view the UN's effectiveness in preventing major 21st-century conflicts as a qualified, yet ultimately insufficient, success. While the UN has successfully mediated numerous smaller crises and provided humanitarian aid, its structural limitations, particularly the veto power of the Security Council, have repeatedly paralyzed it when facing great power rivalries. Therefore, it is often seen as a necessary but fundamentally constrained body, incapable of stopping conflicts driven by geopolitical ambition.",
